|Name gloss=Violation
|Comments=The word khalaf has a wide semantic field in Persian. It could mean "show opposition" or to "object"(khalaf or mukhalefat karadan: demonstrate disagreement), deceit (khalaf-gu: lier, deceit-sayer), criminal (khalaf-kar: violation-doer), crime (khalaf mortakeb-shudan: committing an act of crime), antagonistic (khalaf-e haq: antagonistic towards justice), immoral (khalaf-e shar': violation of sharia, Muslim ethics and laws. As such this frame can correspond with various English frames depending on context: Immoral action and crime),
